","1579":"1579","1601":"1601","1600":"1600","1622":"1622","1633":"1633","1621":"1621","1555":"1555","1587":"1587","1586":"1586","1585":"1585","about 1555":"okolo 1555","about 1586":"okolo 1586","about 1581":"okolo 1581","1659":"1659","between 7 July 1601 and 8 June 1603":"od 7. července 1601 do 8. června 1603","1603":"1603","East Bergholt, Suffolk, England":"East Bergholt, Suffolk, Anglie","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1555–between 7 July 1601 and 8 June 1603":"omkring 1555–fra 7. juli 1601 til 8. juni 1603","1555–1603":"1555–1603","1579–1633":"1579–1633","1586–1659":"1586–1659","1590–1621":"1590–1621","1590–1622":"1590–1622","1555–1601":"1555–1601","1571":"1571","1590":"1590","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1579":"1579","1601":"1601","1600":"1600","1622":"1622","1633":"1633","1621":"1621","1555":"1555","1587":"1587","1586":"1586","1585":"1585","about 1555":"omkring 1555","about 1586":"omkring 1586","about 1581":"omkring 1581","1659":"1659","between 7 July 1601 and 8 June 1603":"fra 7. juli 1601 til 8. juni 1603","1603":"1603","East Bergholt, Suffolk, England":"East Bergholt, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"nl":{"about 1555–between 7 July 1601 and 8 June 1603":"circa 1555–van 7 juli 1601 to 8 juni 1603","1555–1603":"1555–1603","1579–1633":"1579–1633","1586–1659":"1586–1659","1590–1621":"1590–1621","1590–1622":"1590–1622","1555–1601":"1555–1601","1571":"1571","1590":"1590","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1579":"1579","1601":"1601","1600":"1600","1622":"1622","1633":"1633","1621":"1621","1555":"1555","1587":"1587","1586":"1586","1585":"1585","about 1555":"circa 1555","about 1586":"circa 1586","about 1581":"circa 1581","1659":"1659","between 7 July 1601 and 8 June 1603":"van 7 juli 1601 to 8 juni 1603","1603":"1603","East Bergholt, Suffolk, England":"East Bergholt, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"en":{"about 1555–between 7 July 1601 and 8 June 1603":"about 1555–from 7 July 1601 to 8 June 1603","1555–1603":"1555–1603","1579–1633":"1579–1633","1586–1659":"1586–1659","1590–1621":"1590–1621","1590–1622":"1590–1622","1555–1601":"1555–1601","1571":"1571","1590":"1590","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1579":"1579","1601":"1601","1600":"1600","1622":"1622","1633":"1633","1621":"1621","1555":"1555","1587":"1587","1586":"1586","1585":"1585","about 1555":"about 1555","about 1586":"about 1586","about 1581":"about 1581","1659":"1659","between 7 July 1601 and 8 June 1603":"from 7 July 1601 to 8 June 1603","1603":"1603","East Bergholt, Suffolk, England":"East Bergholt, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Allerton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","habitational name from any of several places so called. Allerton on Merseyside, Chapel Allerton in Yorkshire, and others in Yorkshire were named in Old English as <i>alra tūn</i> ‘settlement by the alders’. One in Somerset (<i>Alwarditone</i> in Domesday Book) is ‘Ælfweard's settlement’; one in Yorkshire (Allerton Mauleverer, <i>Alvertone</i> in Domesday Book) is ‘Ælfhere's settlement’.","(Suffolk): probably a variant of   Alderton  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Alderton","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of a number of places called Alderton. Those in Suffolk and Shropshire (<i>Alretuna</i> in Domesday Book) are named with Old English <i>alor</i> + <i>tūn</i>, meaning ‘the settlement by the alders’. Those in Gloucestershire, Northamptonshire, and Wiltshire are named with the Old English personal name <i>Ealdhere</i>, meaning ‘settlement associated with Ealdhere’. The one in Essex contains a different personal name, probably the woman's name Æthelwaru. In England, the surname is most common in East Anglia, making the places in Suffolk and Essex the most likely sources."]}]},{"name":"Bartholomew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of New Testament origin, the name of an apostle mentioned in all the synoptic gospels (Matthew, Mark, and Luke) and in the Acts of the Apostles. It is an Aramaic formation meaning ‘son of Talmai’, and has been assumed by many scholars to be a byname of the apostle   Nathaniel .  <i>Talmai</i> is a Hebrew name, said to mean ‘abounding in furrows’ (Numbers 13:22)."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705202,"age":3,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":14,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705206,"age":16,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705207,"age":30,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705208,"age":32,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705210,"age":45,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Bartholomew Allerton was born about 1555, in Suffolk, England. He married Mary about 1581, in East Bergholt, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 2 daughters. In 1609, his occupation is listed as tailor in Ipswich, Suffolk, England. He died from 7 July 1601 to 8 June 1603, in East Bergholt, Suffolk, England."},"et":{"about 1555–between 7 July 1601 and 8 June 1603":"umbes 1555–7. juuli 1601 kuni 8. juuni 1603","1555–1603":"1555–1603","1579–1633":"1579–1633","1586–1659":"1586–1659","1590–1621":"1590–1621","1590–1622":"1590–1622","1555–1601":"1555–1601","1571":"1571","1590":"1590","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1579":"1579","1601":"1601","1600":"1600","1622":"1622","1633":"1633","1621":"1621","1555":"1555","1587":"1587","1586":"1586","1585":"1585","about 1555":"umbes 1555","about 1586":"umbes 1586","about 1581":"umbes 1581","1659":"1659","between 7 July 1601 and 8 June 1603":"7. juuli 1601 kuni 8. juuni 1603","1603":"1603","East Bergholt, Suffolk, England":"East Bergholt, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"about 1555–between 7 July 1601 and 8 June 1603":"noin 1555–vuodesta 7. heinäkuuta 1601 vuoteen 8. kesäkuuta 1603","1555–1603":"1555–1603","1579–1633":"1579–1633","1586–1659":"1586–1659","1590–1621":"1590–1621","1590–1622":"1590–1622","1555–1601":"1555–1601","15